<plot>APOCRYPHAL HARMONY - The geometric and arithmetic revelations concerning the map of Ancient Hellas (Greece) in relation to the map of the Cosmos. The great mysteries of the ancient temples, the magic of the 'curves' of the Parthenon, the 'Golden Mean' as exemplified in ancient theatres, the relationships of distances between temples. All this, together with the 'hidden harmonies' and the sense of beauty which characterise the religion, art, philosophies, spatial arrangements and language of Ancient Hellas.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?617109</url></doc>
